    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="The refugee population is mainly composed of persons from&#10;Colombia, El Salvador, Cuba, Nicaragua and Venezuela. Especially&#10;during the last two years the asylum claims form Venezuela and, in&#10;particular, Nicaragua, have dramatically increased.&#10;At the same time mixed movements entering through Darien (border&#10;with Colombia) increased during 2019 (more than 23,000 people1&#10;)&#10;with small numbers requesting international protection in Panama,&#10;whilst most others transiting northward through Panama. During the&#10;COVID-19 pandemic, over 2,000 persons remain in the Reception&#10;Centers in Darien and Chiriquí since March due to border closures&#10;to prevent the spread of the virus."/>
    <cas:View sofa="1" members="8 19 24 29 34 39 52 65 78 91 104 117 130 143 156 169 182 195 208 221 234 247 260 273 286 299 312 325 338 351 364 377 390 403 416 429 442 455 468 481 494 507 520 533 546 559 572 585 598 611 624 637 650 663 676 689 702 715 728 741 754 767 780 793 806 819 832 845 858 871 884 897 910 923 936 949 962 975 988 1001 1014 1027 1040 1053 1066 1079 1092 1105 1118 1131 1144 1157 1170 1183 1196 1209 1222 1235 1248 1261 1274 1287 1300 1313 1326 1339 1352 1365 1378 1391 1404 1417 1430 1443 1456 1469 1482 1495 1508 1521 1534 1539 1551 1556 1561 1580 1585 1590 1609 1544 1566 1573 1602 1595 1614 1628 1621 1631 1624 1635 1648"/>
